The eMalahleni resident was last seen and heard of on Friday, when he picked up a newly bought motorcycle from Bike City in Middelburg. He initially arranged to have the motorcycle dropped off at his residence before changing plans and collecting it himself on Friday afternoon. He left his vehicle, a light blue Toyota Yaris, at the dealership and left with the motorcycle, a new jacket and helmet as well as a backpack containing clothes.The last communication he made was a WhatsApp message confirming that he would be home by 14:30. Mr Newton’s brother, Clive Newton, told www.mobserver.co.za that his brother has still not been found and no new information or possible leads have surfaced.Mike Bolhuis Specialised Security Services was approached to aid in his search. Mr Anthony Newton’s physical description is as follows:Hair: Short, light brownEyes: GreenWeight: 104 kgHeight: 1.98 He also has a red prayer string (Kabbalah) tied around his right wrist. Anyone with information that could assist in his search is urged to please call specialist investigator Callie de Kock on 061 419 4416.